The paper discusses an algorithmic problem related to reasoning about causal dependencies in mathematical equations, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI) as well as in statistical inference and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the potential applications of causal ordering in large-scale hypothesis management and analytics, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents an algorithmic solution that involves computing transitive closure, which is a common technique in graph theory and network analysis, making cs.SI (social and information networks) another likely sub-category.
